The fact that the infrared absorption frequency of deuterium chloride (DCl) is shifted from that of hydrogen chloride (HCl) is due to the differences in their what? The difference in their absorption frequencies is due to the difference in their molecular weights. Deuterium chloride has a molecular weight of 18 while hydrogen chloride has a molecular weight of 12.
What is the basic functional unit of skeletal muscle tissue? The basic functional unit of skeletal muscle tissue is the muscle fiber.

The supplementation of diet with which fat soluble vitamins has been shown to reduce cardiovascular disease? There is no definitive answer to this question as the results of studies vary. Some studies have shown that supplementation with fat soluble vitamins can reduce cardiovascular disease risk, while others have not found this to be the case. Ultimately, it is difficult to say whether or not supplementation with fat soluble vitamins is effective in reducing cardiovascular disease risk.
